A STOP and search operation conducted in Tsakane, Ekurhuleni brought results that surprised even the cops. They found two victims stuffed in the boots of hijacked cars and arrested the suspects on the spot. Sergeant Harry Manaka of Duduza police said two victims were rescued from their cars during the stop and search conducted by Duduza and Tsakane police. “The first car was a Hyundai i20 stopped on Malandela road. Police found the victim tied up in the boot of a car hijacked in Heidelberg,” he said. He said the suspects were charged with hijacking and kidnapping. Manaka said another suspect was bust in Langaville driving a hijacked BMW 3 series. The suspect was with two accomplices who fled on foot. Manaka said when they searched the vehicle they found the owner in the boot of his BMW. A third suspect was nabbed during a joint operation by Tsakane police and the EMPD, when he was driving a white Toyota Corolla hijacked in Kagiso, Mogale City. A fourth suspect linked to hijacking a Nissan Almera robbed from Egyptians who were in Tsakane on business was also arrested. The victims who was in the Hyundai i20 thanked God for sparing his life. “I don’t know what could have happened to me if the police did not conduct the operation,” he said. He said his car was hijacked in Heidelberg after two suspects approached him at the robots and pointed guns at him. Tsakane police station commander Colonel Khumbulani Mbatha commended the members for their hard work.